Sometimes when our eyes see something, we may interpret it very differently in our minds.  Technology has become more and more consuming with each passing day.  With information being exchanged faster than it ever has before, I've personally noticed that people's patience is all but non existent.  With the rise of social media more and more people simply want small clips of information that they now accept as truth without actually doing any due dilligence of their own.  Whatever is presented in an image or a short clip is now factual and the truth.
